VLess than 5,000 microbial species
p53
aVhave been characterized as of two years ago,
p54
aVand so we decided to do something about it.
p55
aVAnd we started the Sorcerer II Expedition,
p56
aVwhere we were, as with great oceanographic expeditions,
p57
aVtrying to sample the ocean every 200 miles.
p58
aVWe started in Bermuda for our test project,
p59
aVthen moved up to Halifax,
p60
aVworking down the U.S. East Coast,
p61
aVthe Caribbean Sea, the Panama Canal,
p62
aVthrough to the Galapagos, then across the Pacific,
p63
aVand we're in the process now of working our way
p64
aVacross the Indian Ocean.
p65
aVIt's very tough duty; we're doing this on a sailing vessel,
p66
aVin part to help excite young people
p67
aVabout going into science.
p68
aVThe experiments are incredibly simple.
p69
aVWe just take seawater and we filter it,
p70
aVand we collect different size organisms on different filters,
p71
aVand then take their DNA back to our lab in Rockville,
p72
aVwhere we can sequence a hundred million letters
p73
aVof the genetic code every 24 hours.
p74
aVAnd with doing this,
p75
aVwe've made some amazing discoveries.
